# SOW and Contractual Document Rules

- Clearly define scope, out-of-scope items, and boundaries.
- Use precise, unambiguous language for deliverables and responsibilities.
- Include:
  - Deliverables list
  - Milestones
  - Acceptance criteria
  - Assumptions
  - Dependencies
  - Exclusions
- Avoid vague verbs like “support,” “assist,” or “ensure” unless defined.
- Never introduce contractual commitments without explicit instruction.
- Highlight risks and mitigation strategies.
